Senior Director, Sales Strategy & Enablement
Sunnyvale, CA
About Ceribell

Ceribell is a medical technology company focused on transforming the diagnosis and management of patients with serious neurological conditions. The Ceribell System is a novel, point-of-care electroencephalography (“EEG”) platform specifically designed to address the unmet needs of patients in the acute care setting, and is being used in hundreds of community hospitals, large academic facilities and major IDN's across the country. Our entire team is driven by a shared commitment to transforming the landscape of critical care through our rapid seizure detection technology, come join the movement!

Position Overview:

We are seeking an experienced leader to drive Ceribell’s same store sales business. You will be a core leader for our same store sales business, driving strategy, operations, and enabling our sales organization to perform at their fullest – both for our current product portfolio and new products to come.

What you'll do:

Same store sales strategy 

Develop key strategies around our SSG business
Conduct rigorous analytics on what is driving same store sales and how to grow our business 
Leverage data and analytics to improve account / provider targeting and engagement
Create and manage program around our same store business including EMR integration, protocolization, attrition defense 
Leverage new AI tool to optimize and improve sales process efficiency 
Same store sales operations 

Manage core same store business process – account retention / attrition, quota setting, territory alignment 
Create core sales operations plans (territory, targeting, quotas) 
Develop tools, KPIs, targets, and reporting mechanisms for our same store sales business 
Design incentive programs and monitor their impact 
New product sales enablement 

Work with product and go-to-market (GTM) to define a plan to launch and grow our new Delirium and neonate products 
Develop tools, KPIs, targets, and reporting mechanisms for our new product launches 
Build in the operating and tracking mechanisms to learn and adjust our strategy
Create core sales operations plans (territory, targeting, quotas) and support comp (working with comp resources)
Sales Partner Development and Relationship Management

Build credibility and trusted relationships across the sales organization, especially with the account management VPs and RVPs 
Partner closely with the sales training team to ensure your programs are embedded with the sales organization 
Team management

Coach and develop sales ops analyst and sales enablement manager
What We're Looking For: 

5+ years of experience a top tier management consulting or professional services firm, focusing on transformation and implementation, including managing teams
3+ years of experience managing teams 
2+ years of experience as an operator preferred
Innate curiosity—you investigate anomalies, ask the right questions, and push beyond surface-level explanations
Strong judgment and integrity, balancing efficiency with the rigor required for sensitive compensation processes
Analytical skills, including automation, complex formulas
Clear communicator who can translate complex logic or compensation structures to non-technical stakeholders
Adaptability and drive to thrive in a fast-paced, evolving environment
Ownership mindset 
